    text: "Phone Answering conducts full electrical conversations. Missed Call Text Back covers edge scenarios — a call during a critical termination, a phone at the bottom of a loft ladder, or a single-ring disconnect. Together: zero lost electrical leads."
  }
];

const faqs = [
  {
    question: "When does the missed call text send?",
    answer: "Within seconds of the unanswered ring ending — before the main contractor scrolls to the next NICEIC electrician in his contact list. During full-day containment and cabling runs where your entire team works in ceiling voids and wall cavities, this automatic text keeps your firm commercially visible without anyone descending from the running position."
  },
  {
    question: "What does the text message say?",
    answer: "You draft the wording at onboarding and change it at any time. An electrician-specific message reads: 'Thank you for calling [company name]. We are currently wiring on site. We will return your call at the earliest opportunity. Reply with your electrical requirements for a faster response.' This conveys active installation capability while inviting specifications."
  },
  {
    question: "Does this replace AI Phone Answering?",
    answer: "Both channels defend your electrical business as complementary layers. Phone Answering holds detailed conversations — diagnosing EICR failures, capturing first-fix specifications, and recording commercial fit-out requirements. Missed Call Text Back handles uncommon edge cases — a call during a critical consumer unit termination where breaking concentration risks cross-wiring, a phone in the van while you test circuits inside, or a caller disconnecting before the AI connects. Running both eliminates electrical lead loss completely."
  },
  {
    question: "How much does Missed Call Text Back cost?",
    answer: `This add-on is £${pricing.addOn.price}/month. A full rewire generates £3,000 to £8,000. Recovering one missed call from a facilities manager with twelve-property EICR compliance programme — through a branded text while you verified RCD trip times on another board — initiates a revenue pipeline that surpasses the channel cost for years.`
  },
  {
    question: "Do callers reply to the text?",
    answer: "Main contractors reply with programme details — 'first fix 8 plots Carterton, containment + carcass, consumer units with RCBOs, start next Monday, call me.' Homeowners reply with project summaries — 'rewire 1930s semi, old fuse box, 3 beds, Summertown.' Landlords reply with compliance needs — 'EICR on 6 rentals, certificates expiring, Cowley.' These electrical leads arrive on your dashboard while the Megger finishes the test sequence."
  },
  {
    question: "How is missed call data stored?",
    answer: "All caller details, text replies with property addresses, EICR requirements, circuit specifications, and contact numbers are encrypted on UK and EU servers under UK GDPR. Only you access the data. Nothing reaches competing electrical contractors or any third party."
  }
